{"cursor":"11806","size":14,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Chimeras' (or 'chimaeras') in botany are usually single organisms composed of\ntwo genetically different types of tissue. They occur in plants, on the same\ngeneral basis as with animal chimeras. However, unlike animal chimeras, both\ntypes of tissues may have originated from the same zygote, and the difference is\noften due to mutation during ordinary cell division.\n","linknr":219,"url":"Chimera_(plant)","recorded":1362900700,"links":18,"instances":["shrub","plant","genetics","genetics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Botany"],"headings":["Derivation","Types of plant chimera","Propagation","Chimeras in plant transformation","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e4/Aesculus-hippocastanum-sectorial-chimera.JPG/220px-Aesculus-hippocastanum-sectorial-chimera.JPG","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Ficus_benjamina_leaves.jpg/220px-Ficus_benjamina_leaves.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/04/Ficus.Benjamina.Chimera.jpg/250px-Ficus.Benjamina.Chimera.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Taxus-mosaic1.JPG/220px-Taxus-mosaic1.JPG","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["chimera","genetics"],["chimera","mythology"],["broom","shrub"],["cutting","plant"],["transformation","genetics"],["chimera","genetics"]],"members":["broom","cutting","transformation","chimera"],"related":["Botany","Plant","Chimera_(gen